==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Auk
<hw>Auk</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>alk</ets>; akin to Dan. <ets>alke</ets>, Icel. & Sw.
<ets>alka</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A name given to various
species of arctic sea birds of the family <fam>Alcid⟦ae⟧</fam>. The
great auk, now extinct, is <spn>Alca impennis</spn> (<it>or</it>
<spn>Plautus impennis</spn>) . The razor-billed auk is <spn>Alca
torda</spn>. See <er>Puffin</er>, <er>Guillemot</er>, and
<er>Murre</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aukward</ent>⟦br⟧
